page.title: 06FARM TRAIL DESCRIPTION
page.content: THERE ARE MANY LOVELY ANIMALS AT THE FARM TRAIL.THERE ARE BEAUTIFUL BLACK AND WHITE RABBITS,AND PLENTY OF GOATS.BEFORE YOU GO IN YOU CAN BUY FEED FOR THE ANIMALS.AS YOU APPROACH THE DUCKS,THEY MAKE A LOUD CHATTERING NOISE,BEGGING FOR FOOD.AS YOU THROW THE FOOD DOWN THE DUCKS CLAMBER OVER ONE ANOTHER TO REACH IT.THERE ARE SOME COWS INCLUDING JERSEYS.TWO TURKEYS STRUT AROUND THE PLACE.BEAUTIFUL PONIES ARE IN SOME FIELDS AND DOVES ARE IN THE ORCHARD.THERE IS ALSO AN OLD LIBRARY WHICH HAS IMFORMATION ABOUT THE ESTATE,BUILT IN 1780.
